# Ghost-racing multiplayer relay (Supabase Realtime). Copy this file to
# `.env` (or set these in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables)
# to let two people on DIFFERENT networks see each other ski.
#
# Without these, same-device tabs still connect (via the browser's built-in
# BroadcastChannel) — enough to test locally, but not to race a friend across
# the internet.
#
# The anon/public key is SAFE to expose in a website — that's what it's for.
# Get both from your Supabase project: Settings → API.
#   • Project URL      → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#   • anon public key  → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
